getProcessByIdNoUpdate

protected IAeBusinessProcess getProcessByIdNoUpdate(long aId)
                                             throws AeBusinessProcessException
Returns the business process with the specified process id, locking the process into memory. Each call to getProcessByIdNoUpdate(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to releaseProcess(IAeBusinessProcess). Calling getProcessByIdNoUpdate(long) instead of getProcessById(long) asserts that the caller will not modify the process, so that the process manager may discard the process from memory after it is released without updating its persistent representation (if there is one).

Parameters:
aId -
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException
